//! **WASM Boundary Module — ABI-safe structure-only exports**
//!
//! This module implements the WASM 4 Process Mining Compatibility boundary,
//! making evidence admission, loss accounting, and graduation signals
//! available to browser/Node.js via `wasm-bindgen`.
//!
//! ## Covenant
//!
//! **Compat carries the evidence. `wasm4pm` adjudicates it.**
//!
//! This boundary exports **only**:
//! - Admission gates (parse → admit → refusal with named laws)
//! - Loss accounting (lossy projections with mandatory LossReport)
//! - Graduation signals (typed reasons to escalate to wasm4pm engine)
//!
//! It **forbids** all algorithmic execution:
//! - No discovery (Alpha, Inductive Miner, etc.)
//! - No token replay / conformance checking
//! - No alignment computation
//! - No OCPQ query execution
//! - No receipt minting
//! - No benchmarking gates
//!
//! Any attempt to bypass this covenant results in a compile error
//! (via forbidden function name patterns).
//!
//! ## Marshaling & Serialization
//!
//! - **Primary**: `serde-wasm-bindgen` (binary, preserves u64 precision)
//! - **Fallback**: `serde_json` (debugging only; loses u64 precision > 2^53)
//! - **TypeScript**: `#[tsify]` generates .d.ts from Rust types
//!
//! ## Feature Gate
//!
//! The `wasm` feature (default) enables these exports. When disabled,
//! the module still compiles but exports nothing.

